00:31:25.350 --> 00:31:28.760
Fish-- we covered--

00:31:28.760 --> 00:31:31.410
again, it's a panoptic film.

00:31:31.410 --> 00:31:33.400
We are connecting the
dots between a whole lot

00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:35.840
of different perspectives.

00:31:35.840 --> 00:31:40.240
We set out to find the
truth about what's going on.

00:31:40.240 --> 00:31:42.940
But all we found
were perspectives.

00:31:42.940 --> 00:31:44.914
A scientist would have
a different perspective.

00:31:44.914 --> 00:31:47.080
A villager would have a
different-- the same valley,

00:31:47.080 --> 00:31:48.700
the same river, the
same water-- we're

00:31:48.700 --> 00:31:49.942
talking about the same issue.

00:31:49.942 --> 00:31:51.650
There are so many
different perspectives.

00:31:51.650 --> 00:31:54.850
And this fish is
also a perspective.

00:31:54.850 --> 00:31:57.160
So we covered that as well.

00:31:57.160 --> 00:31:59.710
And we covered a little bit of
Northeastern Himalaya as well.

00:31:59.710 --> 00:32:04.060
The same sort of issues
are taking place, if not

00:32:04.060 --> 00:32:04.900
more dramatic.

00:32:04.900 --> 00:32:09.150
Because the Brahmaputra
