00:32:09.150 --> 00:32:11.260
And then there's the
dark side of coal, which

00:32:11.260 --> 00:32:15.160
is the second 1/3 of the film.

00:32:15.160 --> 00:32:18.610
And then there's rise
of solar and wind.

00:32:18.610 --> 00:32:21.590
So I'll move on to--

00:32:24.335 --> 00:32:26.420
oh, the making of "SunGanges."

00:32:26.420 --> 00:32:28.290
So when I finished
the film-- and this

00:32:28.290 --> 00:32:30.500
is an independent
production completely.

00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:33.524
When I finished the film,
my peers and people said,

00:32:33.524 --> 00:32:34.190
it's a big deal.

00:32:34.190 --> 00:32:35.930
And I didn't know
about it actually.

00:32:35.930 --> 00:32:40.790
So it's hard to just list
out, on hindsight, what we did

00:32:40.790 --> 00:32:43.220
to finish this entire feature.

00:32:47.220 --> 00:32:50.460
We did not know the story
when we began filming.

00:32:50.460 --> 00:32:52.680
We had these questions.

00:32:52.680 --> 00:32:54.270
But the answers
would make the story

00:32:54.270 --> 00:32:56.550
that the film would be about.

00:32:56.550 --> 00:32:57.720
We didn't know the answers.

00:32:57.720 --> 00:33:04.530
So there was a downside to
it, that a lot of wastage

00:33:04.530 --> 00:33:07.620
happened-- that we covered
a whole lot of things

00:33:07.620 --> 00:33:10.580
about hundreds of
hours of footage

00:33:10.580 --> 00:33:14.310
and that had to be
condensed into, say, an hour

00:33:14.310 --> 00:33:17.070
and 1/2 or less.

00:33:17.070 --> 00:33:21.910
And it was like taming a
wild beast on the edit table.

00:33:21.910 --> 00:33:26.250
So in case any of you are
thinking of making a film,

00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:29.940
knowing your story would
be a good way to start.

00:33:29.940 --> 00:33:31.920
Not knowing is also
good, because then you

00:33:31.920 --> 00:33:36.030
approach the project with
a really, really open mind.

00:33:36.030 --> 00:33:36.900
We listened a lot.

00:33:36.900 --> 00:33:38.340
We listened to everybody.

00:33:38.340 --> 00:33:40.350
We listened to the
children in the village.

00:33:40.350 --> 00:33:41.520
We listened to the tribals.

00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:42.811
We listened to the researchers.

00:33:42.811 --> 00:33:45.360
We listened to the boy who
served us in the restaurant.

00:33:45.360 --> 00:33:46.920
We listened to everybody.

00:33:46.920 --> 00:33:49.740
And that really, really helped
get more and more perspective

00:33:49.740 --> 00:33:52.350
into the film.

00:33:52.350 --> 00:33:53.909
We did not wait for
stuff to happen.

00:33:53.909 --> 00:33:55.200
We did not wait for the grants.

00:33:55.200 --> 00:33:56.670
We did not wait
for emails-- people

00:33:56.670 --> 00:33:57.780
to get back with their emails.

00:33:57.780 --> 00:33:58.988
We did not wait for anything.

00:33:58.988 --> 00:34:01.560
We just plunged into the
deep end with the camera

00:34:01.560 --> 00:34:04.440
and whatever little that we had.

00:34:04.440 --> 00:34:07.920
We made full use of our
ignorance about the subject,

00:34:07.920 --> 00:34:10.679
about what's going on.

00:34:10.679 --> 00:34:14.820
And that is probably because
of why the film turned out

00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:17.274
to be the way it is right now.

00:34:17.274 --> 00:34:18.690
And we stayed
stubborn throughout.

00:34:18.690 --> 00:34:22.020
It took about 4 and
1/2 years to make.

00:34:22.020 --> 00:34:25.570
And it got ready
of late last year.

00:34:25.570 --> 00:34:32.712
And it made a European premiere
in Germany early this year.

